chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA if you have Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease. This is also known as hereditary motor and sensory neuropathy (HMSN) or peroneal muscular atrophy (PMA).
chunks.plain_content:
Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease and driving
You must tell DVLA if you have Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease. This is also known as hereditary motor and sensory neuropathy (HMSN) or peroneal muscular atrophy (PMA).

chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you do not tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.
chunks.plain_content:
Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease and driving
You can be fined up to £1,000 if you do not tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.

chunks.html_content: Fill in form CN1 and send it to DVLA to report your disease. The address is on the form.
chunks.plain_content:
